 There are numerous diseases which can irreversibly stiffen the whole spine or parts of the axial skeleton. Due to didactic reasons one can distinguish 3 gropus of such disorders: -  Paradigmatic diseases of the spine with an inherent proneness to stiffness. -  Rare diseases which involve a certain danger of stiffening the spine. -  Rigidity of the spine due to scientifically unrecognised morphologic phenomena.  
